# **ğŸš€ Best Practices for IAM Users**
âœ” **Use IAM roles instead of users for AWS services** â€“ Reduces security risks.  
âœ” **Enable MFA for all IAM users, especially root users**.  
âœ” **Grant least privilege access** â€“ Users should have only necessary permissions.  
âœ” **Rotate access keys regularly** to prevent security vulnerabilities.  
âœ” **Monitor IAM user activity using AWS CloudTrail**.  
âœ” **Use IAM Groups** to manage multiple users efficiently.  
âœ” **Avoid using the Root User account** for daily operations.  

